title: Sketchbook Folio, "Waves Breaking on Rocks with Cliffs and Possible Fog", 1870–85
medium: Graphite on cream wove paper, bound
provenance: Anna Richards Brewster, Scarsdale, NY, 1905-1952; William T. Brewster
creditline: Gift of the National Academy of Design from the Mrs. William T. Brewster Bequest
description: Rough waves crash against three rocks in left middleground. In left background, tall, lightly-sketched cliffs fade out at the right, possibly into a fog bank.
